Bangkok in November, London in April and Stockholm in May.; "Skiers have mountain ranges, tennis players have resorts, why can't a runner take a marathon vacation?"
In addition to air fare and hotel, runners are guaranteed spots in restricted entry races such as the London Marathon.
Berlin's race (Sept. 27, 1992) has grown with the demise of the wall.; "Most marathons take you through cities, so you get a chance to see things you'd never see on a sightseeing bus," said Fred Lebow, president of the New York Roadrunner's Club and director of the New York Marathon.
